The paper discusses a novel swarm intelligent algorithm based on the collective adaptation of a social swarm, inspired by the natural mechanisms of eusocial insects and bacteria. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) or Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), as these fields often deal with swarm intelligence and collective behavior. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of self-organized computational approaches and stigmergic concepts, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents results on the performance of the proposed algorithm in Dynamic Optimization problems, which could also place it in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
